            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">3. A 25 year-old man is shot with a 22 caliber revolver. The entrance wound is in the anterior, lateral aspect of his thigh and the bullet is seen on X ray films to be embedded in the muscle poster lateral to femur. The emergency department physician cleans the wound thoroughly. Which of the following is most appropriate next step in the management?</p>"
