            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">24. A 45 year old man comes to the emergenct department because of severe flank pain that began suddenly 3 hours ago.the pain comes in waves  and radiate down to the ipsilateral testis.His temprature is 37C(98.6F).Dip stick examination of urine is positivefor hematuria.Urinary Ph is 5.8.Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in diagnosis?</p>"
