            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">83. A 19-year-old woman broke her femur 3 days ago during a college soccer tryout. This morning her mother brought her to the ED because she was short of breath. Physical examination reveals a confused patient who is awake but not alert or oriented and a splotchy magenta rash around the base of the neck and back. ABG reveals a P02 under 60 mm Hg.<br />\nWhat is the most likely diagnosis?</p>"
