            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">89. A 58-year-old woman presents to her primary care doctor for evaluation of left knee pain. The pain has been present in both knees for approximately 10 years and has steadily worsened to the point where she can no longer walk. She requires pain medications daily and has difficulty walking as far as the bathroom. On physical exam, she has an antalgic gait. What is the most likely diagnosis?</p>"
