            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">94. A 43-year-old woman was texting while driving when she lost control of her car and ran into a tree. She is<br />\ncomplaining of chest pain; physical examination reveals pallor, cool extremities, a heart rate of 120 bpm, and JVD.<br />\nBlood pressure is 80/40. Chest x-ray reveals 3 broken ribs over the left side of the chest.<br />\nWhich of the following is the most likely type of shock?</p>"
